<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-19T15:59:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-19T15:59:00-05:00" n="414" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">792.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/1–2254: Telegram</note>
                        <head>No. 414<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary
                                    of State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in
                                    Thailand</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-19T15:59:00-05:00">February 19, 1954—3:59
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1646. Your 1524.<note n="1" xml:id="d414fn1">Telegram 1524, Jan. 22,
                                conveyed information regarding the estimated costs and procedures
                                involved in the proposed Saraburi-Ban Phai highway. (792.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/1–2254)</note> Saraburi-Ban Phai
                            Highway discussed top level <gloss target="#t_OCB1">OCB</gloss> meeting
                            Feb 17 by agencies concerned. Agreed jointly (1) approve for planning
                            purposes principle of highway construction; (2) stronger reasons
                            especially military required to justify high enough priority to secure
                            funds for financing; (3) imperative that Thai Govt also ardently desire
                            highway and accordingly make formal request through usual channels.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>